464
00:27:27,260 --> 00:27:28,460
No, I think we need to be...

465
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:30,260
I know we need to celebrate the moment.

466
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:33,380
Yeah, but you're absolutely right.
No team photo for second and third.

467
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:36,520
[Wolff] Barcelona was one race.

468
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:40,240
I don't wanna grab on to one single straw

469
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:42,100
and see all the positiveness in that.

470
00:27:42,140 --> 00:27:44,960
[reporter] Do you see the light
at the end of the tunnel?

471
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:48,120
Um...

472
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:58,720
[Patrick] The person with the most amount
of pressure on them is going to be Toto.

473
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:03,560
He can't promise that, you know,
we're gonna win the championship again.

474
00:28:04,420 --> 00:28:06,380
He can't promise we're gonna win races.

475
00:28:07,140 --> 00:28:09,720
The best thing
that Toto can guarantee Lewis

476
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:11,900
is that he's gonna listen to him.

477
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:31,360
[Hamilton] Boss.

478
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:37,280
Got good pictures around.

479
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:44,520
Who would've thought we would be
where we are in the world today?

480
00:28:46,980 --> 00:28:51,320
Last year, the development of the car,
you weren't happy with me.

481
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,280
[both chuckle]

482
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:56,540
Yeah.

483
00:28:57,180 --> 00:29:00,180
You know, sticking to the concept
from last year,

484
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:03,060
holding on to it because of
the encouraging results at the end...

485
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:05,060
-That's the biggest failure.
-[Wolff] The biggest.

486
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,460
Um...

487
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:08,900
Because last year
lead us in the wrong, you know...

488
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,560
Yeah.

489
00:29:12,840 --> 00:29:15,140
[Wolff] The time has come
to cut our losses

490
00:29:15,180 --> 00:29:18,320
and say that the concept of this car
is never gonna work.

491
00:29:18,360 --> 00:29:20,080
We gotta change it for next year.

492
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:23,360
For me, personally,

493
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:28,000
you know, when you see the step
that Aston Martin made over the winter,

494
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:31,180
shows that if we get it right
with the concept of the car,

495
00:29:31,220 --> 00:29:33,100
you know, the aero and the balance,

496
00:29:33,140 --> 00:29:34,700
we can win a championship.

497
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:40,620
But I don't want to wait until 2026
when we have the new engine regulations.

498
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:42,240
[Hamilton] Frick, me neither.

499
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:45,880
You can be here for, like, 20 more years,
30 more years.

500
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,560
I can't. [laughs]

501
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:48,620
Well, who says that?

502
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,820
This is precious years for me.

503
00:29:53,740 --> 00:29:54,700
I don't know.

504
00:29:56,260 --> 00:29:58,400
Lewis, you're much more
than a racing driver.

505
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,380
Much more
than the seven-time world champion.

506
00:30:01,420 --> 00:30:05,440
You are one of the... the people
that lead this team forward.

507
00:30:18,820 --> 00:30:21,460
[camera shutter clicks]

508
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,800
[melancholy music plays]

509
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:28,720
[Hamilton] I've worked with Toto now...

510
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,060
Uh, I think this is my tenth year
with the team.

511
00:30:31,100 --> 00:30:33,100
[melancholy music continues]

512
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,480
[Hamilton] I've learned
a huge amount from him,

513
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:41,260
and I'd like to think
there's at least one or two things

514
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:43,740
that he may have learned from me.

515
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:53,160
[Wolff] In every relationship,

516
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:58,220
you will have moments
where your objectives may differ.

517
00:30:59,540 --> 00:31:01,320
It's just part of how life goes.

518
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,200
In the context of our relationship,

519
00:31:06,180 --> 00:31:07,180
he's a loyal guy.

520
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:12,140
[Hamilton] Toto and I
have a lot in common.

521
00:31:12,180 --> 00:31:15,200
We're both massively competitive
and hate losing.

522
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,360
Okay, we've had two difficult years,

523
00:31:20,140 --> 00:31:23,860
but... I still have so much belief

524
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:27,100
that Mercedes
and all these people within this team

525
00:31:27,140 --> 00:31:29,200
have the ability to build a great car.

526
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:33,960
You've just got to take a leap of faith.

527
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:37,980
[cell phone chimes]

528
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:45,300
[reporter 1] <i>Lewis Hamilton
has signed a new two-year contract.</i>

529
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:52,520
[Wolff] The thought of Lewis at Ferrari
in a red overall,

530
00:31:53,060 --> 00:31:54,140
it wouldn't suit him.

531
00:31:56,840 --> 00:32:00,180
[reporter 2] <i>The seven-time world champion
has signed a new two-year contract</i>

532
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:02,880
<i>with Mercedes until 2025.</i>

533
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:06,460
[Hamilton] Toto, he's listened.

534
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:12,760
And there just never feels like a time
where I'm not gonna be a Mercedes driver.

535
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:15,080
That's my home. It's my family.

536
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:17,380
[woman] Bye-bye.

537
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:21,780
-[Hamilton] Let's go. See you next week.
-[man] See you next week. Take care.

538
00:32:28,560 --> 00:32:30,980
[Wolff] If I would have a glass ball,
to say to you,

539
00:32:31,020 --> 00:32:33,660
"I am delivering the eighth title,"
would be foolish.

540
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,560
Um, what I can guarantee is

541
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:38,380
that the team
is gonna be giving its utmost

542
00:32:38,420 --> 00:32:42,160
to bring that eighth title to him
that he deserves.

543
00:32:43,820 --> 00:32:45,780
But at the moment,
the most important thing

544
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:48,680
is to finish second
in the Constructors Championship.

545
00:32:49,180 --> 00:32:50,820
Beat Aston Martin and Ferrari.

546
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:53,460
And... And that will be the aim now.

547
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:05,260
{\an8}[Szafnauer] Our season so far
has been disappointing.

548
00:33:05,300 --> 00:33:07,000
[commentator 3] <i>There's contact!</i>

549
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:07,940
[Ocon] I got hit, guys.

550
00:33:07,980 --> 00:33:09,920
[commentator 3] <i>Double DNF for Alpine.</i>

551
00:33:09,960 --> 00:33:11,140
[Gasly] For fuck's sake.

552
00:33:11,180 --> 00:33:12,800
[Szafnauer] I have to do better.

553
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,380
The buck will stop with me.

554
00:33:14,420 --> 00:33:15,760
{\an8}[producer] Three, two, one, go.

555
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:16,840
{\an8}[Ricciardo] I'm back.

556
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,420
It was good.

557
00:33:18,460 --> 00:33:20,000
I got nothing to lose.

558
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:23,100
The dream for me is to...
to get back at Red Bull Racing.

559
00:33:23,140 --> 00:33:24,000
[Padros] <i>Be careful.</i>

560
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:27,260
[commentator 4] <i>The worst thing Ferrari
could do is start racing each other.</i>

561
00:33:27,300 --> 00:33:28,760
[commentator 3] <i>And Leclerc locks up!</i>

562
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:31,660
We need to get results
if we want to survive.

563
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:34,180
[closing theme music plays]

564
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:02,120
[music fades]

